<paragraph blockId="3.[211,1172,511,670]" box="[211,319,511,534]" pageId="3" pageNumber="1259">
<heading box="[211,319,511,534]" fontSize="10" level="3" pageId="3" pageNumber="1259" reason="5">
<emphasis box="[211,319,511,534]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="1259">Diagnosis</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[211,1172,511,670]" pageId="3" pageNumber="1259">
The subgenus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bernhauer" authorityYear="1903" box="[394,533,550,574]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Leptochirus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="1259" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Tropiochirus">
<emphasis box="[394,533,550,574]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="1259">Tropiochirus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be distinguished from all other subgenera of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Germar" authorityYear="1824" box="[211,341,582,606]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Leptochirus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="1259" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[211,341,582,606]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="1259">Leptochirus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the median sulcus on the frons (
<figureCitation box="[735,863,582,606]" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="4.[143,210,1188,1210]" captionTargetBox="[145,1102,167,1155]" captionTargetId="figure-6@4.[145,1102,167,1155]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Figure 1. Leptochirus (Tropiochirus) proteus. (A) Head and prothorax, dorsal view; (B) head and protorax, dorsal view; (C) left and right mandible, dorsal view; (D) labrum, dorsal view; (E) head and protorax, lateral view; (F) metaventrite and sternite III, ventral view. Scale bars: (A, B, E) = 1.0 mm, (C, D) = 0.25 mm, (F) = 0.5 mm." pageId="3" pageNumber="1259">Figures 1A</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[875,935,582,606]" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="5.[211,278,1629,1651]" captionTargetBox="[238,1145,161,1595]" captionTargetId="figure-5@5.[238,1145,161,1596]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Figure 2. Head and protorax of Leptochirus (Tropiochirus). (A) L. (T.) helleri; (B) L. (T.) marina sp. nov. holotype; (C) L. (T.) mery sp. nov. holotype; (D) L. (T.) milton sp. nov. holotype; (E) L. (T.) pachoensis; (F) L. (T.) proteus; (G) L. (T.) venezuelanus; (H) L. (T.) yunganus; (I) L. (T.) zischkaianus. Scale bars = 1.0 mm." pageId="3" pageNumber="1259">2A–I</figureCitation>
), the apex of prosternal process dilated as a circular plate behind the procoxa (
<figureCitation box="[848,960,614,638]" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="4.[143,210,1188,1210]" captionTargetBox="[145,1102,167,1155]" captionTargetId="figure-6@4.[145,1102,167,1155]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Figure 1. Leptochirus (Tropiochirus) proteus. (A) Head and prothorax, dorsal view; (B) head and protorax, dorsal view; (C) left and right mandible, dorsal view; (D) labrum, dorsal view; (E) head and protorax, lateral view; (F) metaventrite and sternite III, ventral view. Scale bars: (A, B, E) = 1.0 mm, (C, D) = 0.25 mm, (F) = 0.5 mm." pageId="3" pageNumber="1259">Figure 1B</figureCitation>
) and the outer and inner lateral teeth of head fused resembling a transverse septum (
<figureCitation box="[939,1066,646,670]" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="4.[143,210,1188,1210]" captionTargetBox="[145,1102,167,1155]" captionTargetId="figure-6@4.[145,1102,167,1155]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Figure 1. Leptochirus (Tropiochirus) proteus. (A) Head and prothorax, dorsal view; (B) head and protorax, dorsal view; (C) left and right mandible, dorsal view; (D) labrum, dorsal view; (E) head and protorax, lateral view; (F) metaventrite and sternite III, ventral view. Scale bars: (A, B, E) = 1.0 mm, (C, D) = 0.25 mm, (F) = 0.5 mm." pageId="3" pageNumber="1259">Figures 1A</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1079,1140,646,670]" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="5.[211,278,1629,1651]" captionTargetBox="[238,1145,161,1595]" captionTargetId="figure-5@5.[238,1145,161,1596]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Figure 2. Head and protorax of Leptochirus (Tropiochirus). (A) L. (T.) helleri; (B) L. (T.) marina sp. nov. holotype; (C) L. (T.) mery sp. nov. holotype; (D) L. (T.) milton sp. nov. holotype; (E) L. (T.) pachoensis; (F) L. (T.) proteus; (G) L. (T.) venezuelanus; (H) L. (T.) yunganus; (I) L. (T.) zischkaianus. Scale bars = 1.0 mm." pageId="3" pageNumber="1259">2A–I</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
